{
  "stem": "1677.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father had only one leg.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was a highly decorated soldier in the First World War, and lost his leg at the Italian front.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my happiest childhood memories, there were two-- the German governesses, who came all from the Sudetenland.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they were telling us, Kitty, you have nothing to worry.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When our Fuhrer will come into power, I will protect you, because you speak such a beautiful German.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You will never pose as a Jew.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was so convinced that they will come to my rescue that there is a great percentage of my survival stamina in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I waited for Tant and Mimi to turn up suddenly and get me out of the mess.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the second happiest memory was Sunday afternoon, was chamber music.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father played the cello, which was taller than him.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother was singing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Frau Nettle, German, played the piano.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Mr.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Outie, a Slovak policeman, the flute.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And every Sunday afternoon, to my greatest boredom, we sat in little white nursery chairs with my sister, Eva, with little white aprons.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Everybody was swimming, or playing balls, or doing anything.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had to listen to, and always the end of the concert, my father played from the [NON-ENGLISH] by-- on cello.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was-- and my mother sang it-- and that was the end of the performance.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, he had his own chamber.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was his chamber quintet, which he brought into life.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he came by the House of Rothschild, from Vienna.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was a foreign language correspondent.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And because he was a war-damaged person, he got preferential treatment, and was sent to Puchov, a break off of Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then he heads to manage a factory, ironically, for asbestos roof covering.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
